# Payments Domain – Local Setup Guide

# Purpose

This document explains how to set up and run the Payments Domain locally. It covers required tools, environment configuration, bootstrapping steps, and common issues encountered during setup.

The goal is to enable developers to run the full Payments stack in a local environment that closely mirrors production behavior.

---

# Prerequisites

Before starting, ensure the following tools are installed:

## Required Tools

* Java 17+ (or Kotlin-compatible JDK)
* Maven or Gradle build tool
* Docker & Docker Compose
* Git
* cURL or Postman (for API testing)

## Optional Tools

* Kafka UI (for event inspection)
* PostgreSQL client (e.g., DBeaver, pgAdmin)
* IDE (IntelliJ IDEA recommended)

## Infrastructure Dependencies

The Payments Domain depends on the following local services:

* PostgreSQL (Payments database)
* Kafka (event streaming)
* Redis (idempotency / caching layer)
* Mock Payment Provider service (for PSP simulation)

---

# Environment Variables

The following environment variables must be configured before running the service.

## Core Configuration

| Variable      | Description                  | Example                                     |
| ------------- | ---------------------------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| `APP_ENV`     | Runtime environment          | `local`                                     |
| `SERVER_PORT` | API service port             | `8080`                                      |
| `DB_URL`      | PostgreSQL connection string | `jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/payments` |
| `DB_USER`     | Database username            | `payments_user`                             |
| `DB_PASSWORD` | Database password            | `password`                                  |

---

## Kafka Configuration

| Variable               | Description            | Example           |
| ---------------------- | ---------------------- | ----------------- |
| `KAFKA_BROKERS`        | Kafka broker addresses | `localhost:9092`  |
| `KAFKA_TOPIC_PAYMENTS` | Payment events topic   | `payments-events` |

---

## Redis Configuration

| Variable     | Description | Example     |
| ------------ | ----------- | ----------- |
| `REDIS_HOST` | Redis host  | `localhost` |
| `REDIS_PORT` | Redis port  | `6379`      |

---

## Payment Provider Configuration

| Variable         | Description            | Example                 |
| ---------------- | ---------------------- | ----------------------- |
| `PSP_MOCK_URL`   | Mock provider endpoint | `http://localhost:9000` |
| `PSP_TIMEOUT_MS` | Provider timeout       | `3000`                  |

---

## Security (Local Only)

| Variable        | Description                    | Example |
| --------------- | ------------------------------ | ------- |
| `AUTH_DISABLED` | Disable auth for local testing | `true`  |

